# vais-web live-deploy 4-platform credential template (master-plan v76).
#
# Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in values to activate the live-deploy
# suite. With all 7 vars set, INTEGRITY reports `WEB RUNTIME smoke=77/77`
# instead of the credential-skipped default `61/77`. Each platform suite
# (cloudflare/vercel/netlify/aws-lambda) has 4 vitest `it` cases — total
# 16 tests gated by these credentials.
#
# Default INTEGRITY (no creds) keeps `describe.skip` — the gate stays
# green at 61/77. Setting all credentials does NOT regress the default
# (skip-mode CI keeps reporting 61/77 unless test runner explicitly
# loads .env). Set `RUN_LIVE_DEPLOY=1` (or your CI's equivalent) and
# load .env before running `bash scripts/check-integrity.sh` to exercise
# the live path.
#
# The deploy scripts under `scripts/{platform}-live-deploy.sh` create a
# unique resource per run (worker name / vercel project / netlify site /
# lambda function with a `vais-web-live-{timestamp}-{rand}` prefix) and
# `trap cleanup EXIT` deletes the resource on script exit, so live runs
# don't accumulate cloud state across CI runs.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cloudflare Workers (workers.dev)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#   - CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN: dashboard.cloudflare.com → My Profile →
#     API Tokens → Create Token → "Edit Cloudflare Workers" template.
#     Token needs Workers Scripts:Edit permission on the target account.
#   - CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID: dashboard.cloudflare.com → Workers & Pages
#     overview → "Account ID" in the right sidebar.
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Vercel
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#   - VERCEL_TOKEN: vercel.com/account/tokens → Create Token. The default
#     "Full account" scope is sufficient; for a tighter scope use a
#     team-specific token with Deployment Read/Write permission only.
VERCEL_TOKEN=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Netlify
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#   - NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN: app.netlify.com/user/applications → Personal
#     access tokens → New access token. Sites:Write scope required for
#     `netlify deploy`.
NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AWS Lambda
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#   - AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID + AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY: an IAM user with
#     `AWSLambda_FullAccess` (or a tightly-scoped policy granting
#     lambda:CreateFunction / DeleteFunction / InvokeFunction +
#     iam:PassRole on the role below).
#   - AWS_LAMBDA_ROLE_ARN: an existing role the lambda will assume,
#     typically `arn:aws:iam::<account>:role/lambda-basic-execution`
#     with the `AWSLambdaBasicExecutionRole` managed policy attached.
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
AWS_LAMBDA_ROLE_ARN=
